  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7105 trading below the GEX flip at 7114, dealers are in negative gamma territory and will amplify moves lower by selling delta as price declines. The massive negative gamma wall at 7115 (-7025M) sits just above current levels, creating resistance as dealers need to sell rallies back toward this strike. If price pushes above 7114-7115, dealers flip to positive gamma mode and will provide support by buying dips toward the 7100 level (+4404M).\n\nKey levels: 7115 negative gamma resistance above, 7100 positive gamma support below, with 7200 (+7589M) as the major positive gamma ceiling if we break higher.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect choppy action with downside bias unless we reclaim 7115, then look for bounce back toward 7150.",
